summary: The caller is frustrated with the quality of a product they bought and would like to make a complaint. They are transferred from agent to agent, and the call becomes very protracted as the details of the complaint are clarified. It is finally decided that the complaint will be forwarded to the relevant team for further processing and that the caller will receive a complaint number via WhatsApp, along with instructions to send supporting photos of the product and packaging to the same WhatsApp number.
speaker_a_summary: The user calls ITC to follow up on a complaint and is transferred to the executive who had been talking to them earlier. The executive checks with them for a minute and then puts them on hold to check something else, which takes another minute. They are then transferred to a customer care agent who will handle the complaint, but the agent is busy and the user is put on hold. The user is informed that the agent will be available after a minute, but then the call ends.
speaker_b_summary: Himani wants to confirm a 40kg packet of ITC Farmland FTW PN G59, with a packaging date of 18th of July 2023. Himani's packet has a hole, so she needs a new one sent to her via home delivery. The complaint is registered and the complaint number is provided. Himani needs to send a photo of the defective packet, including the front and back side and any visible details like the batch number. Himani is also asked to provide a photo of the product once it arrives. Himani is very pleased with the service and will be available for the call.
